fields.descriptive_line: Album consisting of manuscript text, drawings and tracings, and plates, collated from a variety of sources on Near Eastern antiquities. 1820-1830. Mostly copies after Cornelius de Bruyn and other artists including James Bruce, Dominique Vivant Denon, Frederick Norden, Sir Robert Ker Porter

fields.historical_context_note:
The album is roughly divisible into 6 parts [SD.184:1-6]. Regarding transcripts, tracings and copies, the compiler of the album may have used alternative editions of the publications mentioned. For attribution of the album to Sir Robert Ker Porter, see Searight Archive.
The Temple of Taffeh depicted is now located in the Rijksmuseum van Oudheden in Leiden, Netherlands.
